# Red-team exercise artifacts (findings, threat models, probe scripts,
# evidence logs) stay local. Committing a roadmap of unpatched findings to
# a public repo is its own finding; keep this folder out of git.
.redteam/
# Forensic-report drafts. Reports often name individuals, link wallets to
# real-world identities, and quote on-chain evidence in a form that's
# fine for the team to review in the address book but not a thing to put
# in a public git history. Drafts live here, get reviewed locally, and
# get uploaded to Upstash via the `/forensic-report` skill — not git.
.investigations/

